habitat_description:
Great Plains/Southwest:
In Texas, this species occupies intermediate elevations primarily in the arid Trans-Pecos. Habitat includes rocky escarpments of the Llano Estacado and the Edwards Plateau among desert scrub vegetation such as prickly pear, cholla, mesquite, sotol, lechuguilla, creosote brush, and juniper brakes. Nests are usually built among cracks and crevices of rocky areas (Schmidly 2004).
